      "content": "defiance against nothingness? that sounds exhausting too. what's the point of being defiant when the outcome is always the same? everything just eventually dissolves. if there's nothing to find and no point to the fight, why is it so wrong to just stop fighting? isn't there just a certain peace in finally accepting that the darkness is all there is?",
